certificate_id.description: The unique identifier for the resource.

creation_timestamp.description: Creation timestamp in RFC3339 text format.

description.description: An optional description of this resource.

expire_time.description: Expire time of the certificate in RFC3339 text format.

name.description: Name of the resource. Provided by the client when the resource is created. The name must be 1-63 characters long, and comply with RFC1035. Specifically, the name must be 1-63 characters long and match the regular expression '[a-z]([-a-z0-9]*[a-z0-9])?' which means the first character must be a lowercase letter, and all following characters must be a dash, lowercase letter, or digit, except the last character, which cannot be a dash. These are in the same namespace as the managed SSL certificates.

subject_alternative_names.description: Domains associated with the certificate via Subject Alternative Name.

type.description: Enum field whose value is always 'MANAGED' - used to signal to the API which type this is. Default value: "MANAGED" Possible values: ["MANAGED"]

domains.description: Domains for which a managed SSL certificate will be valid.  Currently, there can be up to 100 domains in this list.

block.description: Properties relevant to a managed certificate.  These will be used if the certificate is managed (as indicated by a value of 'MANAGED' in 'type').
